      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can think of it as the lactic acid molecules \"interfering\" with the normal flow of electrical signals within the muscle cells. Imagine the electrical signals as a complex network of cabled wires, and the lactic acid molecules as a chemical blob that gets stuck in the cable insulation, disrupting the signal transmission. This can cause the muscle fibers to misfire, leading to the characteristic burning sensation. The affected muscle cells become desynchronized, allowing them to contract and relax irregularly, contributing to the pain.",
      "source": "target",
